===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}

According to {{zh-ref|Lin Yiguang (1920)}}, this character is an ancient form of {{och-l|經}}. Its [[w:Chinese bronze inscriptions|bronze inscription]] form resembles vertical threads passing through the top of a sewing machine and has the meaning "to abide by, to comply with".

[[w:Shuowen Jiezi|''Shuowen'']] analyzes this character as streams of water across land.

